Uttar Pradesh is located in northern India immediately to the east of the
capital, New Delhi. - Mod.CP]
******
[2] India
Date: 9 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Polio eradication website [edited]
<http://www.polioeradication.org/content/general/LatestNews200611.asp>

India: outbreak on decline at epicenter, campaigns to minimize further spread
-----------------------------------------------
The polio outbreak this year [2006] that spread into polio-free parts of
India appears to have peaked in its original epicenter in western Uttar
Pradesh. The red line in the graph [please go the web link shown above to
see the graph] shows cases rising in Moradabad and JP Nagar districts of
the state, the start of the outbreak. The successive color lines show the
poliovirus moving beyond this epicenter to a gradually expanding area. In
the 1st wave of affected areas (defined by the red, green and blue lines),
cases have started to fall, evidence that the origins of the outbreak are
slowing, while its effects continue to rise in the final wave of affected
areas, delineated in pink.
Supplementary immunization campaigns take place the week of 12 Nov [2006]
and have been expanded to nearly half the country in response to the
outbreak, covering affected districts, neighboring districts and states
considered at high risk. This outbreak has seen India's cases rise 10-fold
over the same period in 2005 and has dealt a serious blow to India's
remarkable progress in 2005. Eradication is within India's grasp: every
district in the country has been polio-free at some point in time. With
sustained immunization campaigns that reach all vulnerable children, India
can achieve this status in all districts at the same time.
--
