[3] Cameroon
Date: 13 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Polio eradication website [edited]
<http://www.polioeradication.org/casecount.asp>

Following pre-notification last week, the type 3 case from northern
Cameroon (bordering Borno state in northeastern Nigeria) has now been
officially reported.
The case investigation is ongoing. The child has family both in Cameroon
and Nigeria. It is unclear whether the onset of paralysis occurred in
Nigeria or in Cameroon. The child had recently arrived in Cameroon with his
family from Nigeria.
An emergency immunization response is currently being planned by the
government of Cameroon. While finalized dates are not yet confirmed, the
immunization response will likely be conducted in the next 4 weeks.
[For a good map of the affected area in Cameroon, see
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/cameroon_pol98.jpg>,
and for a map of Nigeria, including Borno state, see
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/nigeria_pol93.jpg>.
- Mod.MPP]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[With respect to the ongoing polio activity in India, according to the
Southeast Asian Regional Office (SEARO) of WHO, as of today, 13 Nov 2006,
there were 32 new polio cases reported in India during this past week
<http://www.searo.who.int/EN/Section1226.asp>,
bringing the 2006 case total to 522, as compared with a total of 66 cases
reported for 2005 and 134 cases reported for 2004. The most recent date of
onset of a polio case with a wild polio virus isolated was 7 Oct 2006.
Information on the dates of onset of these 32 new cases reported this past
week was not available, so one is unable to tell whether the dates of onset
were more recent than 7 Oct 2006. Clearly, there has been a significant
outbreak in India this year [2006]. In our last posting on this outbreak
(on 3 Oct 2006), there had been 312 cases reported, so in the intervening 6
weeks, there have been an additional 210 cases reported.
With respect to the reported case of type 3 polio from Cameroon, it is as
yet unclear what is the origin of this virus (Nigeria vs. Cameroon), and we
await the results of genetic testing on the isolate as well as the full
investigation to understand more the epidemiology of this case. According
to the polio eradication website, type 3 poliovirus has been identified in
Pakistan, India, Afghanistan, Nigeria, Niger and Cameroon during 2006, with
dates of onset in Cameroon 22 Aug 2006 and in Nigeria 18 Sep 2006 (most
recent case). One suspects that the case in Cameroon is related to
poliovirus transmission in Nigeria, but until more information is
available, this is a supposition and not confirmed. - Mod.MPP]
